				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Coupling, the Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Coupling, the Game is The ultimate party game in which you will discover more about your friends in 45 minutes than you did in your whole life, AND have a blast at the same time! It's a game for stronger friendships, deep conversations and a fun evening, with a healthy amount of competition, lots of laughter, a pinch of tickling and, for the most playful, a bit of singing and dancing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basic version of the game contains 10 mini-games on 120 COUPLING cards, which, combined with unique mechanics, make a highly dynamic game. More than 500 combinations of questions and challenges break even the toughest ice and ensure that the game is still fun even after you play it with the same group of friends for the tenth time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You play the game in three stages:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Like in life, every player starts out as single. Then, through random questions and fun personal stories, you couple up with two players.&amp;#10;     These two players now compete for your affection in the second stage through exciting challenges: charades with sounds, mouth reading, recipes and geometric shapes and lines. &amp;#10;     In the third stage, it&amp;rsquo;s Couples Showdown, where each player competes along with their best partner for a glorious victory against other couples through new mini games: multiple choice cards to challenge your beliefs, personal questions that you may have always wanted to talk about, but didn't dare ask, psychological pictures to see what&amp;rsquo;s beyond obvious, and drawing things and associations to release your inner Picasso. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First couple to get through the FINISH LINE wins and gets to sit in the glorious winning spot!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two players can use the cards to get to know each other better. Additional blank cards can be purchased to expand the game to 12 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
